Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Exzerpte nach Autoren"

  • Bibliographic references with annotations
  • First subfolder (Annotation: "-L"):
    • Extracts from different publications about Rubens' life and artworks
    • Printed extract:" A sailor and his mistress" from "The work of Peter Paul Rubens" by L. Burchard
    • Photos of the chapter "8. Oktober 1926 Herr L. Burchard: Skizzen des jungen Rubens." in "Sitzungs-Berichte der Kunstgeschichtlichen Gesellschaft Berlin (Oktober bis Mai 1927)
    • Photo of the 'Archduke Albert of Austria' portrait attached to the extract "Rubens als Porträtmaler" by Gustav Glück
  • Second subfolder (Annotation: "M-"):
    • Extracts from different publications about Rubens' life and artworks
    • Photos of the chapter "Rubens in Spanien" by Meisel in "Kunstblatt" 3, 1823.
    • Photos of "Plate III" in "Rubens before Italy" by C. Norris
    • Chapter: "De Beteekenis der Prentkunst voor het Rubens-Schilderij" (cut pages from a book)
  • Third folder (Annotation: Excerpte aus dem Bulletin Rubens):
    • Extracts from the 'Rubens Bulletin'
